This paper deals with privacy mechanisms for statistical databases, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the concept of differential privacy, which is a fundamental concept in data privacy and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses utility guarantees and loss functions, which are topics that fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of geometric mechanisms, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
